    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Sense"/>
    <tag group="ProductId" tag="HLCommunit"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cSbSDecInt" name="Deconstruct Intention" description="At 10th level, a spellburst savant can alter the areas of her nova spells. When she casts a nova spell that affects an area, she can cause it to instead affect one of the following areas at the cost of a +1 metamagic adjustment.\n\n• A cone-shaped burst or spread originating from her space, with a length of up to 30 feet.\n\n• A line-shaped burst or spread originating from her space, with a length of up to 120 feet.\n\n• A spread or burst within long range with a radius of up to 20 feet.\n\n• A number of 5-foot cubes within close range equal to the spellburst savant&apos;s Wisdom modifier.\n\n• A ray with long range and a single target. This ray requires a ranged touch attack to hit, and if the spell normally allowed a Reflex save for half damage, it does not do so (though any other effects may still be saved against).\n\nIn addition, the spellburst savant can use a ray or ranged touch attack spell in melee at the cost of a +1 metamagic adjustment. She makes melee touches instead of ranged touches, and the spell otherwise functions as normal." compset="ClSpecial" summary="You can change the area and targeting of spells">
    <tag group="abAction" tag="None"/>
    <tag group="ProductId" tag="HLCommunit"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cSbSDecEff" name="Deconstruct Effect" description="At 15th level, a spellburst savant can adjust the deepest traits defining her nova spells. When she casts a nova spell that prompts a saving throw, she can change that saving throw to another type of save (Fortitude, Reflex, or Will) at the cost of a +1 metamagic adjustment. If the spell prompts multiple saving throws, she can change all of them (even to the same save)." compset="ClSpecial" summary="You can change the saving throw of spells">
    <tag group="abAction" tag="None"/>
    <tag group="ProductId" tag="HLCommunit"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cSbSTruesi" name="Truesight" description="Starting at 17th level, a spellburst savant can see the world for what it truly is. She gains the benefits of the {i}true seeing{/i} spell at all times." compset="ClSpecial" summary="You gain the benefits of {i}true seeing{/i}">
