  <thing id="cSbSFirBon" name="Firearm Bond" description="A gun witch must choose a bonded item as her arcane bond. Her bonded item may be any firearm, and she begins play with either a blunderbuss, musket, or pistol as her bonded item. This starting firearm is battered, and only she knows how to use it properly. All other creatures treat her gun as if it had the broken condition. If the weapon already has the broken condition, it does not work at all for anyone else trying to use it. This starting weapon can only be sold for scrap (it’s worth 4d10 gp when sold).\n\nIn addition, the gun witch gains Gunsmithing as a bonus feat, and can use her class level in place of her base attack bonus for the purposes of meeting requirements and prerequisites." compset="ClSpecial">
